                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.77/31: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bundy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-01T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 1, 1919, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your September 25, 2 p.m.</p>
                <p>You may suggest to Liberian Government that for the present and until the
                    conclusion of loan agreement negotiations they may not wish to give definite
                    consideration to such applications.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
